<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">26</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">3</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">May 1 2006</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">691</span> - <span property="pageEnd">699</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16702448/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">16702448</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2006.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: May 1 2006</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.263055714">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">Fluoroscopy is a useful technique for the detection and characterization of anterior abdominal wall hernias, and radiologists should be familiar with the variety of findings in these hernias as observed in barium studies.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabpanel"><h3>Authors</h3><section class="core-authors"><h4>Affiliations</h4><div id="con1" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Hanna M.</span> <span property="familyName">Zafar</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="a